HEADWORD: Undersecretary
<hw>Un`der*sec"re*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
secretary who is subordinate to the chief secretary; an assistant
secretary; <as>as, an <ex>undersecretary</ex> of the
Treasury</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

